programme.desc: Martin Roberts' senses are set tingling at a London flat, Dion Dublin bangs the drum for a semi-detached property in Crewe and Martel Maxwell an end-of-terrace in County Durham

programme.title: Escape to the Country: West Yorkshire
programme.desc: Ginny Buckley helps a theatre couple swap London life for a West Yorkshire home with rural sparkle and then meets a family who started a bold new life on a 30-acre farm

programme.title: Rick Stein's Australia
programme.desc: Rick travels south from the dry outback into the Riverina, a region that has been transformed from barren plains into one of Australia's most important food bowls. Shaped by irrigation and enriched by waves of migration, the Riverina tells a story of reinvention that is reflected in its farming, wine, culture and cuisine

programme.title: BBC News: 04/02/2026
programme.desc: The latest national and international stories as they break

programme.title: Politics Live: 04/02/2026
programme.desc: The latest stories from Westminster and beyond

programme.title: Bridge of Lies
programme.desc: Netti, Lee, Abigail and Star compete for cash by crossing a bridge of stepping stones across the studio floor. Quiz show, hosted by Ross Kemp

programme.title: Unbeatable
programme.desc: Jason Manford presents the general knowledge quiz in which four contestants compete over three rounds to find a single 'unbeatable' answer and streak ahead of the rest to make the final where they can win a cash prize

programme.title: The Boss
programme.desc: Quiz hosted by Susan Calman in which one contestant becomes the Boss and has to use judgement and tactics to decide which player is best suited to answer questions

programme.title: The Vintage French Farmhouse
programme.desc: Jo Roberts, Ian Humphries and Harry Khwaja are in Sommieres in the South of France in search of antiques that will wow their loyal customers and social media followers. Harry tries his best to haggle for a sculptor's stand while Ian thinks a 100-year-old brass and glass lamp will see the offers light up when he comes to sell it. Jo finds a vintage case full of antique lace collars she is certain her followers will love. Harry then sets the group the task of finding something green to sell

programme.title: Who Do You Think You Are? USA: Allison Janney
programme.desc: Award-winning stage, film and TV actress Allison Janney traces her family tree and uncovers a story that ties her to some of America's first British settlers. She learns that the family's journey to North America almost ended in tragedy

programme.title: Japan: Earth's Enchanted Islands: The Southwest Islands
programme.desc: In the south-west of Japan, the Ryukyu Islands stretch towards the tropics and all life on them is influenced by the power of the sea, with volcanos and typhoons forces to be reckoned with. Michelle Dockery narrates a journey beginning at an island at the top of the chain and travelling south, revealing unexpected stories of isolation, unique wildlife and unsolved mysteries

programme.title: Flog It!: Wiltshire 52
programme.desc: Paul Martin presents from Longleat in Wiltshire, where experts Claire Rawle and David Fletcher value items brought in for examination by members of the public, including an autograph album that evokes the glamour of bygone eras and a marble statuette that previously found use as a goal-post for backyard football practice. Paul also gets up close and personal with some of the region's most exotic residents as he relates the history of Longleat Safari Park

programme.title: Richard Osman's House of Games: Week 15: Wednesday
programme.desc: Fatiha El-Ghorri, Patrick Grant, Mr Motivator and Lauren Oakley test their general knowledge skills in a variety of trivia-based games across the week

programme.title: Clive Myrie's African Adventure: Marrakech
programme.desc: In Morocco, Clive travels to Marrakesh, known around the world as the Red City for the red clay buildings that line its streets. He meets a Medina chef whose slow roasted lamb, cooked in underground ovens, has had the Royals of approval. In a souk, he masters the art of creating stunning tile mosaics, learns the skills required to make authentic Moroccan rugs, before spending the night in the High Atlas Mountains

programme.title: Rick Stein's Australia
programme.desc: The chef ends his journey of New South Wales on the south coast, known as the Sapphire Coast for its vibrant deep-blue waters. He explains why it's his favourite region in Australia, enjoys the seafood and looks toward the future

programme.title: Digging for Britain: Medieval Murder and Roman Pets
programme.desc: Featuring a vast first-century Roman compound, the warhorses that changed the course of history, a medieval murder mystery, the thriving farmstead belonging to Isaac Newton's mother, thousands of animal bones from a Roman farm, and a 300-million-year-old forest that built the modern world

programme.title: Reform: Ready to Rule?
programme.desc: With Reform UK consistently leading in the polls, Laura Kuenssberg examines the party's ambitions, organisation and efforts to professionalise. From its origins on the political fringes to representation on local councils and in Westminster, she asks whether Reform UK is ready to be a party of government. Featuring interviews with leading members of the party, the film explores how voter dissatisfaction is reshaping Britain's political landscape

programme.title: One Foot in the Grave: The Eternal Quadrangle
programme.desc: Victor takes up life drawing classes and Margaret is only too happy to see the back of him - until she learns the subject is a nude woman whom he has volunteered to drive home. Comedy, starring Richard Wilson and Annette Crosbie

programme.title: Newsnight: 04/02/2026
programme.desc: Analysis of the day's events, with Victoria Derbyshire

programme.title: Weather: 04/02/2026
programme.desc: The latest forecast

programme.title: Unspun World with John Simpson: 04/02/2026
programme.desc: The BBC's world affairs editor reflects on the week's major global news stories, talking to local experts from around the world to go behind the headlines

programme.title: Till
programme.desc: In August 1955, African-American teenager Emmett Till is abducted and lynched in Mississippi after being accused of offending a white woman. His mother Mamie Till-Mobley vows to expose the racism behind the murder, while working to have those involved brought to justice. Fact-based drama, starring Danielle Deadwyler

programme.title: Pati's Mexican Table

programme.title: Pati's Mexican Table

programme.title: Pati's Mexican Table

programme.title: Pati's Mexican Table
